function color-convert.ansi16.ansi256 (args)

  • description and source-code
    ansi16.ansi256 = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}
  • example usage
    n/a

    hcg.keyword = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}
  • example usage
    n/a

  • example usage
    ...

All 'from' functions have a hidden property called `.channels` that indicates the number of channels the function expects
 (not including alpha).

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

// Hex to LAB
convert.hex.lab('DEADBF');         // [ 76, 21, -2 ]
convert.hex.lab.raw('DEADBF');     // [ 75.56213190997677, 20.653827952644754, -2.290532499330533 ]

// RGB to CMYK
convert.rgb.cmyk(167, 255, 4);     // [ 35, 0, 98, 0 ]
convert.rgb.cmyk.raw(167, 255, 4); // [ 34.509803921568626, 0, 98.43137254901961, 0 ]
```
...

				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}

		if (typeof result === 'object') {

				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}
  • example usage
    ...
Color-convert is a color conversion library for JavaScript and node.
It converts all ways between `rgb`, `hsl`, `hsv`, `hwb`, `cmyk`, `ansi`, `ansi16`, `hex` strings, and CSS `keyword`s (will round
 to closest):

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hsl(140, 200, 100);             // [96, 48, 59]
convert.keyword.rgb('blue');                // [0, 0, 255]

var rgbChannels = convert.rgb.channels;     // 3
var cmykChannels = convert.cmyk.channels;   // 4
var ansiChannels = convert.ansi16.channels; // 1
```

# Install
...

  • description and source-code
    keyword.xyz = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}

			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}
  • example usage

var convert = require('color-convert');

// Hex to LAB
convert.hex.lab('DEADBF');         // [ 76, 21, -2 ]
convert.hex.lab.raw('DEADBF');     // [ 75.56213190997677, 20.653827952644754, -2.290532499330533 ]

// RGB to CMYK
convert.rgb.cmyk(167, 255, 4);     // [ 35, 0, 98, 0 ]
convert.rgb.cmyk.raw(167, 255, 4); // [ 34.509803921568626, 0, 98.43137254901961, 0 ]
```

### Arrays
All functions that accept multiple arguments also support passing an array.

Note that this does **not** apply to functions that convert from a color that only requires one value (e.g. `keyword`, `ansi256`, `
hex`, etc.)
...

All functions that accept multiple arguments also support passing an array.

Note that this does **not** apply to functions that convert from a color that only requires one value (e.g. `keyword`, `ansi256`, `
hex`, etc.)

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hex(123, 45, 67);      // '7B2D43'
convert.rgb.hex([123, 45, 67]);    // '7B2D43'
```

## Routing

Conversions that don't have an _explicitly_ defined conversion (in [conversions.js](conversions.js)), but can be converted
by means of sub-conversions (e.g. XYZ -> **RGB** -> CMYK), are automatically routed together. This allows just about any
 color model supported by `color-convert` to be converted to any other model, so long as a sub-conversion path exists. This is also
 true for conversions requiring more than one step in between (e.g. LCH -> **LAB** -> **XYZ** -> **RGB** ->
Hex).
...

function color-convert.rgb.hsl (args)

  • description and source-code
    rgb.hsl = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}
  • example usage
    ...

Color-convert is a color conversion library for JavaScript and node.
It converts all ways between `rgb`, `hsl`, `hsv`, `hwb`, `cmyk`, `ansi`, `ansi16`, `hex` strings, and CSS `keyword`s (will round
 to closest):

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hsl(140, 200, 100);             // [96, 48, 59]
convert.keyword.rgb('blue');                // [0, 0, 255]

var rgbChannels = convert.rgb.channels;     // 3
var cmykChannels = convert.cmyk.channels;   // 4
var ansiChannels = convert.ansi16.channels; // 1
```
...

ansi16 optimization

	if (value === 0) {

  • description and source-code

			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}
  • example usage
    n/a

### Arrays
All functions that accept multiple arguments also support passing an array.

Note that this does **not** apply to functions that convert from a color that only requires one value (e.g. `keyword`, `ansi256`, `
hex`, etc.)

All functions that accept multiple arguments also support passing an array.

Note that this does **not** apply to functions that convert from a color that only requires one value (e.g. `keyword`, `ansi256`, `
hex`, etc.)

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hex(123, 45, 67);      // '7B2D43'
convert.rgb.hex([123, 45, 67]);    // '7B2D43'
```

## Routing

Conversions that don't have an _explicitly_ defined conversion (in [conversions.js](conversions.js)), but can be converted
by means of sub-conversions (e.g. XYZ -> **RGB** -> CMYK), are automatically routed together. This allows just about any
 color model supported by `color-convert` to be converted to any other model, so long as a sub-conversion path exists. This is also
 true for conversions requiring more than one step in between (e.g. LCH -> **LAB** -> **XYZ** -> **RGB** ->
Hex).
...

function color-convert.ansi16.hsl (args)

  • description and source-code
    hsl = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}
  • example usage
    ...

Color-convert is a color conversion library for JavaScript and node.
It converts all ways between `rgb`, `hsl`, `hsv`, `hwb`, `cmyk`, `ansi`, `ansi16`, `hex` strings, and CSS `keyword`s (will round
 to closest):

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hsl(140, 200, 100);             // [96, 48, 59]
convert.keyword.rgb('blue');                // [0, 0, 255]

var rgbChannels = convert.rgb.channels;     // 3
var cmykChannels = convert.cmyk.channels;   // 4
var ansiChannels = convert.ansi16.channels; // 1
```
...

convert.rgb.ansi16 = function (args) {
	var r = args[0];
	var g = args[1];
	var b = args[2];
	var value = 1 in arguments ? arguments[1] : convert.rgb.hsv(args)[2]; // hsv ->
ansi16 optimization

	value = Math.round(value / 50);

	if (value === 0) {
		return 30;
	}

 color model supported by `color-convert` to be converted to any other model, so long as a sub-conversion path exists. This is also
 true for conversions requiring more than one step in between (e.g. LCH -> **LAB** -> **XYZ** -> **RGB** ->
Hex).
...

function color-convert.ansi16.hex.raw (args)

  • description and source-code
    raw = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		return fn(args);
	}
  • example usage
    ...
All 'from' functions have a hidden property called `.channels` that indicates the number of channels the function expects
 (not including alpha).

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

// Hex to LAB
convert.hex.lab('DEADBF');         // [ 76, 21, -2 ]
convert.hex.lab.raw('DEADBF');     // [ 75.56213190997677, 20.653827952644754
, -2.290532499330533 ]

// RGB to CMYK
convert.rgb.cmyk(167, 255, 4);     // [ 35, 0, 98, 0 ]
convert.rgb.cmyk.raw(167, 255, 4); // [ 34.509803921568626, 0, 98.43137254901961, 0 ]
```

module color-convert.ansi16.hsl

function color-convert.ansi16.hsl (args)

  • description and source-code
    hsl = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}
  • example usage
    ...

Color-convert is a color conversion library for JavaScript and node.
It converts all ways between `rgb`, `hsl`, `hsv`, `hwb`, `cmyk`, `ansi`, `ansi16`, `hex` strings, and CSS `keyword`s (will round
 to closest):

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hsl(140, 200, 100);             // [96, 48, 59]
convert.keyword.rgb('blue');                // [0, 0, 255]

var rgbChannels = convert.rgb.channels;     // 3
var cmykChannels = convert.cmyk.channels;   // 4
var ansiChannels = convert.ansi16.channels; // 1
```
...

		}

			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		return fn(args);
	}
  • example usage

All functions that accept multiple arguments also support passing an array.

Note that this does **not** apply to functions that convert from a color that only requires one value (e.g. `keyword`, `ansi256`, `
hex`, etc.)

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hex(123, 45, 67);      // '7B2D43'
convert.rgb.hex([123, 45, 67]);    // '7B2D43'
```

## Routing

Conversions that don't have an _explicitly_ defined conversion (in [conversions.js](conversions.js)), but can be converted
by means of sub-conversions (e.g. XYZ -> **RGB** -> CMYK), are automatically routed together. This allows just about any
 color model supported by `color-convert` to be converted to any other model, so long as a sub-conversion path exists. This is also
 true for conversions requiring more than one step in between (e.g. LCH -> **LAB** -> **XYZ** -> **RGB** ->
Hex).
...

function color-convert.ansi256.hsl (args)

  • description and source-code
    hsl = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}
  • example usage
    ...

Color-convert is a color conversion library for JavaScript and node.
It converts all ways between `rgb`, `hsl`, `hsv`, `hwb`, `cmyk`, `ansi`, `ansi16`, `hex` strings, and CSS `keyword`s (will round
 to closest):

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hsl(140, 200, 100);             // [96, 48, 59]
convert.keyword.rgb('blue');                // [0, 0, 255]

var rgbChannels = convert.rgb.channels;     // 3
var cmykChannels = convert.cmyk.channels;   // 4
var ansiChannels = convert.ansi16.channels; // 1
```
...

			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {

		}

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hex(123, 45, 67);      // '7B2D43'
convert.rgb.hex([123, 45, 67]);    // '7B2D43'
```

## Routing

Conversions that don't have an _explicitly_ defined conversion (in [conversions.js](conversions.js)), but can be converted
by means of sub-conversions (e.g. XYZ -> **RGB** -> CMYK), are automatically routed together. This allows just about any
 color model supported by `color-convert` to be converted to any other model, so long as a sub-conversion path exists. This is also
 true for conversions requiring more than one step in between (e.g. LCH -> **LAB** -> **XYZ** -> **RGB** ->
Hex).
...

function color-convert.ansi256.hex.raw (args)

  • description and source-code
    raw = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		return fn(args);
	}
  • example usage
    ...

    hwb = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}

All 'from' functions have a hidden property called `.channels` that indicates the number of channels the function expects
 (not including alpha).

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

// Hex to LAB
convert.hex.lab('DEADBF');         // [ 76, 21, -2 ]
convert.hex.lab.raw('DEADBF');     // [ 75.56213190997677, 20.653827952644754
, -2.290532499330533 ]

// RGB to CMYK
convert.rgb.cmyk(167, 255, 4);     // [ 35, 0, 98, 0 ]
convert.rgb.cmyk.raw(167, 255, 4); // [ 34.509803921568626, 0, 98.43137254901961, 0 ]
```

  • example usage
    ...
Color-convert is a color conversion library for JavaScript and node.
It converts all ways between `rgb`, `hsl`, `hsv`, `hwb`, `cmyk`, `ansi`, `ansi16`, `hex` strings, and CSS `keyword`s (will round
 to closest):

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hsl(140, 200, 100);             // [96, 48, 59]
convert.keyword.rgb('blue');                // [0, 0, 255]

var rgbChannels = convert.rgb.channels;     // 3
var cmykChannels = convert.cmyk.channels;   // 4
var ansiChannels = convert.ansi16.channels; // 1
```

### Arrays
All functions that accept multiple arguments also support passing an array.

Note that this does **not** apply to functions that convert from a color that only requires one value (e.g. `keyword`, `ansi256`, `
hex`, etc.)

All functions that accept multiple arguments also support passing an array.

Note that this does **not** apply to functions that convert from a color that only requires one value (e.g. `keyword`, `ansi256`, `
hex`, etc.)

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hex(123, 45, 67);      // '7B2D43'
convert.rgb.hex([123, 45, 67]);    // '7B2D43'
```

## Routing

Conversions that don't have an _explicitly_ defined conversion (in [conversions.js](conversions.js)), but can be converted
by means of sub-conversions (e.g. XYZ -> **RGB** -> CMYK), are automatically routed together. This allows just about any
 color model supported by `color-convert` to be converted to any other model, so long as a sub-conversion path exists. This is also
 true for conversions requiring more than one step in between (e.g. LCH -> **LAB** -> **XYZ** -> **RGB** ->
Hex).
...

  • description and source-code
    hsl = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}
  • example usage
    ...

	}
  • example usage
    ...
Color-convert is a color conversion library for JavaScript and node.
It converts all ways between `rgb`, `hsl`, `hsv`, `hwb`, `cmyk`, `ansi`, `ansi16`, `hex` strings, and CSS `keyword`s (will round
 to closest):

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hsl(140, 200, 100);             // [96, 48, 59]
convert.keyword.rgb('blue');                // [0, 0, 255]

var rgbChannels = convert.rgb.channels;     // 3
var cmykChannels = convert.cmyk.channels;   // 4
var ansiChannels = convert.ansi16.channels; // 1
```

...

function color-convert.apple.xyz (args)

  • description and source-code
    xyz = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}

All 'from' functions have a hidden property called `.channels` that indicates the number of channels the function expects
 (not including alpha).

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

// Hex to LAB
convert.hex.lab('DEADBF');         // [ 76, 21, -2 ]
convert.hex.lab.raw('DEADBF');     // [ 75.56213190997677, 20.653827952644754
, -2.290532499330533 ]

// RGB to CMYK
convert.rgb.cmyk(167, 255, 4);     // [ 35, 0, 98, 0 ]
convert.rgb.cmyk.raw(167, 255, 4); // [ 34.509803921568626, 0, 98.43137254901961, 0 ]
```

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hex(123, 45, 67);      // '7B2D43'
convert.rgb.hex([123, 45, 67]);    // '7B2D43'
```

## Routing

Conversions that don't have an _explicitly_ defined conversion (in [conversions.js](conversions.js)), but can be converted
by means of sub-conversions (e.g. XYZ -> **RGB** -> CMYK), are automatically routed together. This allows just about any
 color model supported by `color-convert` to be converted to any other model, so long as a sub-conversion path exists. This is also
 true for conversions requiring more than one step in between (e.g. LCH -> **LAB** -> **XYZ** -> **RGB** ->
Hex).
...

function color-convert.apple.hex.raw (args)

  • description and source-code
    raw = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		return fn(args);
	}
  • example usage
    ...

All 'from' functions have a hidden property called `.channels` that indicates the number of channels the function expects
 (not including alpha).

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

// Hex to LAB
convert.hex.lab('DEADBF');         // [ 76, 21, -2 ]
convert.hex.lab.raw('DEADBF');     // [ 75.56213190997677, 20.653827952644754
, -2.290532499330533 ]

// RGB to CMYK
convert.rgb.cmyk(167, 255, 4);     // [ 35, 0, 98, 0 ]
convert.rgb.cmyk.raw(167, 255, 4); // [ 34.509803921568626, 0, 98.43137254901961, 0 ]
```

Color-convert is a color conversion library for JavaScript and node.
It converts all ways between `rgb`, `hsl`, `hsv`, `hwb`, `cmyk`, `ansi`, `ansi16`, `hex` strings, and CSS `keyword`s (will round
 to closest):

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hsl(140, 200, 100);             // [96, 48, 59]
convert.keyword.rgb('blue');                // [0, 0, 255]

var rgbChannels = convert.rgb.channels;     // 3
var cmykChannels = convert.cmyk.channels;   // 4
var ansiChannels = convert.ansi16.channels; // 1
```

All functions that accept multiple arguments also support passing an array.

Note that this does **not** apply to functions that convert from a color that only requires one value (e.g. `keyword`, `ansi256`, `
hex`, etc.)

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hex(123, 45, 67);      // '7B2D43'
convert.rgb.hex([123, 45, 67]);    // '7B2D43'
```

## Routing

Conversions that don't have an _explicitly_ defined conversion (in [conversions.js](conversions.js)), but can be converted
by means of sub-conversions (e.g. XYZ -> **RGB** -> CMYK), are automatically routed together. This allows just about any
 color model supported by `color-convert` to be converted to any other model, so long as a sub-conversion path exists. This is also
 true for conversions requiring more than one step in between (e.g. LCH -> **LAB** -> **XYZ** -> **RGB** ->
Hex).
...

function color-convert.cmyk.hsl (args)

  • description and source-code
    hsl = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}
  • example usage
    ...

var convert = require('color-convert');

All functions that accept multiple arguments also support passing an array.

Note that this does **not** apply to functions that convert from a color that only requires one value (e.g. `keyword`, `ansi256`, `
hex`, etc.)

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hex(123, 45, 67);      // '7B2D43'
convert.rgb.hex([123, 45, 67]);    // '7B2D43'
```

## Routing

Conversions that don't have an _explicitly_ defined conversion (in [conversions.js](conversions.js)), but can be converted
by means of sub-conversions (e.g. XYZ -> **RGB** -> CMYK), are automatically routed together. This allows just about any
 color model supported by `color-convert` to be converted to any other model, so long as a sub-conversion path exists. This is also
 true for conversions requiring more than one step in between (e.g. LCH -> **LAB** -> **XYZ** -> **RGB** ->
Hex).
...

function color-convert.cmyk.hex.raw (args)

  • description and source-code
    raw = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		return fn(args);
	}

Color-convert is a color conversion library for JavaScript and node.
It converts all ways between `rgb`, `hsl`, `hsv`, `hwb`, `cmyk`, `ansi`, `ansi16`, `hex` strings, and CSS `keyword`s (will round
 to closest):

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hsl(140, 200, 100);             // [96, 48, 59]
convert.keyword.rgb('blue');                // [0, 0, 255]

var rgbChannels = convert.rgb.channels;     // 3
var cmykChannels = convert.cmyk.channels;   // 4
var ansiChannels = convert.ansi16.channels; // 1
```
...

		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types

			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}

### Arrays
All functions that accept multiple arguments also support passing an array.

Note that this does **not** apply to functions that convert from a color that only requires one value (e.g. `keyword`, `ansi256`, `
hex`, etc.)

All functions that accept multiple arguments also support passing an array.

Note that this does **not** apply to functions that convert from a color that only requires one value (e.g. `keyword`, `ansi256`, `
hex`, etc.)

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hex(123, 45, 67);      // '7B2D43'
convert.rgb.hex([123, 45, 67]);    // '7B2D43'
```

## Routing

Conversions that don't have an _explicitly_ defined conversion (in [conversions.js](conversions.js)), but can be converted
by means of sub-conversions (e.g. XYZ -> **RGB** -> CMYK), are automatically routed together. This allows just about any
 color model supported by `color-convert` to be converted to any other model, so long as a sub-conversion path exists. This is also
 true for conversions requiring more than one step in between (e.g. LCH -> **LAB** -> **XYZ** -> **RGB** ->
Hex).
...

function color-convert.gray.hsl (args)

  • description and source-code
    hsl = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}
  • example usage
    ...

Color-convert is a color conversion library for JavaScript and node.
It converts all ways between `rgb`, `hsl`, `hsv`, `hwb`, `cmyk`, `ansi`, `ansi16`, `hex` strings, and CSS `keyword`s (will round
 to closest):

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hsl(140, 200, 100);             // [96, 48, 59]
convert.keyword.rgb('blue');                // [0, 0, 255]

var rgbChannels = convert.rgb.channels;     // 3
var cmykChannels = convert.cmyk.channels;   // 4
var ansiChannels = convert.ansi16.channels; // 1
```
...

convert.rgb.ansi16 = function (args) {
	var r = args[0];
	var g = args[1];
	var b = args[2];
	var value = 1 in arguments ? arguments[1] : convert.rgb.hsv(args)[2]; // hsv ->
ansi16 optimization

	value = Math.round(value / 50);

	if (value === 0) {
		return 30;
	}

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

// Hex to LAB
convert.hex.lab('DEADBF');         // [ 76, 21, -2 ]
convert.hex.lab.raw('DEADBF');     // [ 75.56213190997677, 20.653827952644754
, -2.290532499330533 ]

// RGB to CMYK
convert.rgb.cmyk(167, 255, 4);     // [ 35, 0, 98, 0 ]
convert.rgb.cmyk.raw(167, 255, 4); // [ 34.509803921568626, 0, 98.43137254901961, 0 ]
```

module color-convert.gray.hsl

function color-convert.gray.hsl (args)

  • description and source-code
    hsl = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}
  • example usage
    ...

Color-convert is a color conversion library for JavaScript and node.
It converts all ways between `rgb`, `hsl`, `hsv`, `hwb`, `cmyk`, `ansi`, `ansi16`, `hex` strings, and CSS `keyword`s (will round
 to closest):

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hsl(140, 200, 100);             // [96, 48, 59]
convert.keyword.rgb('blue');                // [0, 0, 255]

var rgbChannels = convert.rgb.channels;     // 3
var cmykChannels = convert.cmyk.channels;   // 4
var ansiChannels = convert.ansi16.channels; // 1
```
...

  • description and source-code
    raw = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		return fn(args);
	}
  • example usage

### Arrays
All functions that accept multiple arguments also support passing an array.

Note that this does **not** apply to functions that convert from a color that only requires one value (e.g. `keyword`, `ansi256`, `
hex`, etc.)

All functions that accept multiple arguments also support passing an array.

Note that this does **not** apply to functions that convert from a color that only requires one value (e.g. `keyword`, `ansi256`, `
hex`, etc.)

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hex(123, 45, 67);      // '7B2D43'
convert.rgb.hex([123, 45, 67]);    // '7B2D43'
```

## Routing

Conversions that don't have an _explicitly_ defined conversion (in [conversions.js](conversions.js)), but can be converted
by means of sub-conversions (e.g. XYZ -> **RGB** -> CMYK), are automatically routed together. This allows just about any
 color model supported by `color-convert` to be converted to any other model, so long as a sub-conversion path exists. This is also
 true for conversions requiring more than one step in between (e.g. LCH -> **LAB** -> **XYZ** -> **RGB** ->
Hex).
...

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}

			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}
  • example usage

};

	var value = 1 in arguments ? arguments[1] : convert.rgb.hsv(args)[2]; // hsv ->
ansi16 optimization

	value = Math.round(value / 50);

	if (value === 0) {

  • example usage
    ...
Color-convert is a color conversion library for JavaScript and node.
It converts all ways between `rgb`, `hsl`, `hsv`, `hwb`, `cmyk`, `ansi`, `ansi16`, `hex` strings, and CSS `keyword`s (will round
 to closest):

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hsl(140, 200, 100);             // [96, 48, 59]
convert.keyword.rgb('blue');                // [0, 0, 255]

var rgbChannels = convert.rgb.channels;     // 3
var cmykChannels = convert.cmyk.channels;   // 4
var ansiChannels = convert.ansi16.channels; // 1
```

  • description and source-code
    xyz = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}

hex`, etc.)

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hex(123, 45, 67);      // '7B2D43'
convert.rgb.hex([123, 45, 67]);    // '7B2D43'
```

## Routing

Conversions that don't have an _explicitly_ defined conversion (in [conversions.js](conversions.js)), but can be converted
by means of sub-conversions (e.g. XYZ -> **RGB** -> CMYK), are automatically routed together. This allows just about any
 color model supported by `color-convert` to be converted to any other model, so long as a sub-conversion path exists. This is also
 true for conversions requiring more than one step in between (e.g. LCH -> **LAB** -> **XYZ** -> **RGB** ->
Hex).
...

function color-convert.hcg.hex.raw (args)

  • description and source-code
    raw = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		return fn(args);
	}
  • example usage
    ...

All 'from' functions have a hidden property called `.channels` that indicates the number of channels the function expects
 (not including alpha).

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

// Hex to LAB
convert.hex.lab('DEADBF');         // [ 76, 21, -2 ]
convert.hex.lab.raw('DEADBF');     // [ 75.56213190997677, 20.653827952644754
, -2.290532499330533 ]

// RGB to CMYK
convert.rgb.cmyk(167, 255, 4);     // [ 35, 0, 98, 0 ]
convert.rgb.cmyk.raw(167, 255, 4); // [ 34.509803921568626, 0, 98.43137254901961, 0 ]
```

function color-convert.hcg.keyword (args)

  • description and source-code
    keyword = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}

  • example usage
    ...
Color-convert is a color conversion library for JavaScript and node.
It converts all ways between `rgb`, `hsl`, `hsv`, `hwb`, `cmyk`, `ansi`, `ansi16`, `hex` strings, and CSS `keyword`s (will round
 to closest):

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hsl(140, 200, 100);             // [96, 48, 59]
convert.keyword.rgb('blue');                // [0, 0, 255]

var rgbChannels = convert.rgb.channels;     // 3
var cmykChannels = convert.cmyk.channels;   // 4
var ansiChannels = convert.ansi16.channels; // 1
```

### Arrays
All functions that accept multiple arguments also support passing an array.

Note that this does **not** apply to functions that convert from a color that only requires one value (e.g. `keyword`, `ansi256`, `
hex`, etc.)

    ansi16 = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}
  • example usage
    ...

	return ansi;
};

convert.hsv.ansi16 = function (args) {
	// optimization here; we already know the value and don't need to get
	// it converted for us.
	return convert.rgb.ansi16(convert.hsv.rgb(args), args[2]);
};

All 'from' functions have a hidden property called `.channels` that indicates the number of channels the function expects
 (not including alpha).

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

// Hex to LAB
convert.hex.lab('DEADBF');         // [ 76, 21, -2 ]
convert.hex.lab.raw('DEADBF');     // [ 75.56213190997677, 20.653827952644754
, -2.290532499330533 ]

// RGB to CMYK
convert.rgb.cmyk(167, 255, 4);     // [ 35, 0, 98, 0 ]
convert.rgb.cmyk.raw(167, 255, 4); // [ 34.509803921568626, 0, 98.43137254901961, 0 ]
```

### Arrays
All functions that accept multiple arguments also support passing an array.

Note that this does **not** apply to functions that convert from a color that only requires one value (e.g. `keyword`, `ansi256`, `
hex`, etc.)

  • example usage
    ...

Color-convert is a color conversion library for JavaScript and node.
It converts all ways between `rgb`, `hsl`, `hsv`, `hwb`, `cmyk`, `ansi`, `ansi16`, `hex` strings, and CSS `keyword`s (will round
 to closest):

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hsl(140, 200, 100);             // [96, 48, 59]
convert.keyword.rgb('blue');                // [0, 0, 255]

var rgbChannels = convert.rgb.channels;     // 3
var cmykChannels = convert.cmyk.channels;   // 4
var ansiChannels = convert.ansi16.channels; // 1
```
...

		}

		}

		return fn(args);
	}

convert.rgb.ansi16 = function (args) {
	var r = args[0];
	var g = args[1];
	var b = args[2];
	var value = 1 in arguments ? arguments[1] : convert.rgb.hsv(args)[2]; // hsv ->
ansi16 optimization

	value = Math.round(value / 50);

	if (value === 0) {
		return 30;
	}

All 'from' functions have a hidden property called `.channels` that indicates the number of channels the function expects
 (not including alpha).

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

// Hex to LAB
convert.hex.lab('DEADBF');         // [ 76, 21, -2 ]
convert.hex.lab.raw('DEADBF');     // [ 75.56213190997677, 20.653827952644754
, -2.290532499330533 ]

  • description and source-code
    xyz = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}

### Arrays
All functions that accept multiple arguments also support passing an array.

Note that this does **not** apply to functions that convert from a color that only requires one value (e.g. `keyword`, `ansi256`, `
hex`, etc.)

All functions that accept multiple arguments also support passing an array.

Note that this does **not** apply to functions that convert from a color that only requires one value (e.g. `keyword`, `ansi256`, `
hex`, etc.)

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hex(123, 45, 67);      // '7B2D43'
convert.rgb.hex([123, 45, 67]);    // '7B2D43'
```

## Routing

Conversions that don't have an _explicitly_ defined conversion (in [conversions.js](conversions.js)), but can be converted
by means of sub-conversions (e.g. XYZ -> **RGB** -> CMYK), are automatically routed together. This allows just about any
 color model supported by `color-convert` to be converted to any other model, so long as a sub-conversion path exists. This is also
 true for conversions requiring more than one step in between (e.g. LCH -> **LAB** -> **XYZ** -> **RGB** ->
Hex).
...

function color-convert.hsl.hsv (args)

  • description and source-code
    hsv = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}
  • example usage
    ...
	return [l, a, b];
};

convert.rgb.ansi16 = function (args) {
	var r = args[0];
	var g = args[1];
	var b = args[2];
	var value = 1 in arguments ? arguments[1] : convert.rgb.hsv(args)[2]; // hsv ->
ansi16 optimization

	value = Math.round(value / 50);

	if (value === 0) {
		return 30;
	}

  • example usage
    ...
Color-convert is a color conversion library for JavaScript and node.
It converts all ways between `rgb`, `hsl`, `hsv`, `hwb`, `cmyk`, `ansi`, `ansi16`, `hex` strings, and CSS `keyword`s (will round
 to closest):

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hsl(140, 200, 100);             // [96, 48, 59]
convert.keyword.rgb('blue');                // [0, 0, 255]

var rgbChannels = convert.rgb.channels;     // 3
var cmykChannels = convert.cmyk.channels;   // 4
var ansiChannels = convert.ansi16.channels; // 1
```

convert.hex.lab('DEADBF');         // [ 76, 21, -2 ]
convert.hex.lab.raw('DEADBF');     // [ 75.56213190997677, 20.653827952644754
, -2.290532499330533 ]

// RGB to CMYK
convert.rgb.cmyk(167, 255, 4);     // [ 35, 0, 98, 0 ]
convert.rgb.cmyk.raw(167, 255, 4); // [ 34.509803921568626, 0, 98.43137254901961, 0 ]
```

    gray = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {

		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {

			}
		}

		return result;
	}

    ...
All functions that accept multiple arguments also support passing an array.

Note that this does **not** apply to functions that convert from a color that only requires one value (e.g. `keyword`, `ansi256`, `
hex`, etc.)

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hex(123, 45, 67);      // '7B2D43'
convert.rgb.hex([123, 45, 67]);    // '7B2D43'
```

## Routing

Conversions that don't have an _explicitly_ defined conversion (in [conversions.js](conversions.js)), but can be converted
by means of sub-conversions (e.g. XYZ -> **RGB** -> CMYK), are automatically routed together. This allows just about any
 color model supported by `color-convert` to be converted to any other model, so long as a sub-conversion path exists. This is also
 true for conversions requiring more than one step in between (e.g. LCH -> **LAB** -> **XYZ** -> **RGB** ->
Hex).
...

function color-convert.hsl.hex.raw (args)

  • description and source-code
    raw = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		return fn(args);
	}

  • example usage
    ...
Color-convert is a color conversion library for JavaScript and node.
It converts all ways between `rgb`, `hsl`, `hsv`, `hwb`, `cmyk`, `ansi`, `ansi16`, `hex` strings, and CSS `keyword`s (will round
 to closest):

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hsl(140, 200, 100);             // [96, 48, 59]
convert.keyword.rgb('blue');                // [0, 0, 255]

var rgbChannels = convert.rgb.channels;     // 3
var cmykChannels = convert.cmyk.channels;   // 4
var ansiChannels = convert.ansi16.channels; // 1
```

    ...
All functions that accept multiple arguments also support passing an array.

Note that this does **not** apply to functions that convert from a color that only requires one value (e.g. `keyword`, `ansi256`, `
hex`, etc.)

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hex(123, 45, 67);      // '7B2D43'
convert.rgb.hex([123, 45, 67]);    // '7B2D43'
```

## Routing

Conversions that don't have an _explicitly_ defined conversion (in [conversions.js](conversions.js)), but can be converted
by means of sub-conversions (e.g. XYZ -> **RGB** -> CMYK), are automatically routed together. This allows just about any
 color model supported by `color-convert` to be converted to any other model, so long as a sub-conversion path exists. This is also
 true for conversions requiring more than one step in between (e.g. LCH -> **LAB** -> **XYZ** -> **RGB** ->
Hex).
...

    hsl = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}
  • example usage
    ...

Color-convert is a color conversion library for JavaScript and node.
It converts all ways between `rgb`, `hsl`, `hsv`, `hwb`, `cmyk`, `ansi`, `ansi16`, `hex` strings, and CSS `keyword`s (will round
 to closest):

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hsl(140, 200, 100);             // [96, 48, 59]
convert.keyword.rgb('blue');                // [0, 0, 255]

var rgbChannels = convert.rgb.channels;     // 3
var cmykChannels = convert.cmyk.channels;   // 4
var ansiChannels = convert.ansi16.channels; // 1
```
...

All 'from' functions have a hidden property called `.channels` that indicates the number of channels the function expects
 (not including alpha).

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

// Hex to LAB
convert.hex.lab('DEADBF');         // [ 76, 21, -2 ]
convert.hex.lab.raw('DEADBF');     // [ 75.56213190997677, 20.653827952644754, -2.290532499330533 ]

// RGB to CMYK
convert.rgb.cmyk(167, 255, 4);     // [ 35, 0, 98, 0 ]
convert.rgb.cmyk.raw(167, 255, 4); // [ 34.509803921568626, 0, 98.43137254901961, 0 ]
```

			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}
  • example usage
    ...

Color-convert is a color conversion library for JavaScript and node.
It converts all ways between `rgb`, `hsl`, `hsv`, `hwb`, `cmyk`, `ansi`, `ansi16`, `hex` strings, and CSS `keyword`s (will round
 to closest):

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hsl(140, 200, 100);             // [96, 48, 59]
convert.keyword.rgb('blue');                // [0, 0, 255]

var rgbChannels = convert.rgb.channels;     // 3
var cmykChannels = convert.cmyk.channels;   // 4
var ansiChannels = convert.ansi16.channels; // 1
```
...

function color-convert.hsv.hsl.raw (args)

  • description and source-code
    raw = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		return fn(args);
	}
  • example usage
    ...
All 'from' functions have a hidden property called `.channels` that indicates the number of channels the function expects
 (not including alpha).

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

// Hex to LAB
convert.hex.lab('DEADBF');         // [ 76, 21, -2 ]
convert.hex.lab.raw('DEADBF');     // [ 75.56213190997677, 20.653827952644754
, -2.290532499330533 ]

// RGB to CMYK
convert.rgb.cmyk(167, 255, 4);     // [ 35, 0, 98, 0 ]
convert.rgb.cmyk.raw(167, 255, 4); // [ 34.509803921568626, 0, 98.43137254901961, 0 ]
```

Note that this does **not** apply to functions that convert from a color that only requires one value (e.g. `keyword`, `ansi256`, `
hex`, etc.)

All functions that accept multiple arguments also support passing an array.

Note that this does **not** apply to functions that convert from a color that only requires one value (e.g. `keyword`, `ansi256`, `
hex`, etc.)

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hex(123, 45, 67);      // '7B2D43'
convert.rgb.hex([123, 45, 67]);    // '7B2D43'
```

## Routing

Conversions that don't have an _explicitly_ defined conversion (in [conversions.js](conversions.js)), but can be converted
by means of sub-conversions (e.g. XYZ -> **RGB** -> CMYK), are automatically routed together. This allows just about any
 color model supported by `color-convert` to be converted to any other model, so long as a sub-conversion path exists. This is also
 true for conversions requiring more than one step in between (e.g. LCH -> **LAB** -> **XYZ** -> **RGB** ->
Hex).
...

function color-convert.hwb.hsl (args)

  • description and source-code
    hsl = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}
  • example usage
    ...

  • example usage
    ...
Color-convert is a color conversion library for JavaScript and node.
It converts all ways between `rgb`, `hsl`, `hsv`, `hwb`, `cmyk`, `ansi`, `ansi16`, `hex` strings, and CSS `keyword`s (will round
 to closest):

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hsl(140, 200, 100);             // [96, 48, 59]
convert.keyword.rgb('blue');                // [0, 0, 255]

var rgbChannels = convert.rgb.channels;     // 3
var cmykChannels = convert.cmyk.channels;   // 4
var ansiChannels = convert.ansi16.channels; // 1
```

All 'from' functions have a hidden property called `.channels` that indicates the number of channels the function expects
 (not including alpha).

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

// Hex to LAB
convert.hex.lab('DEADBF');         // [ 76, 21, -2 ]
convert.hex.lab.raw('DEADBF');     // [ 75.56213190997677, 20.653827952644754
, -2.290532499330533 ]

// RGB to CMYK
convert.rgb.cmyk(167, 255, 4);     // [ 35, 0, 98, 0 ]
convert.rgb.cmyk.raw(167, 255, 4); // [ 34.509803921568626, 0, 98.43137254901961, 0 ]
```

var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hex(123, 45, 67);      // '7B2D43'
convert.rgb.hex([123, 45, 67]);    // '7B2D43'
```

## Routing

Conversions that don't have an _explicitly_ defined conversion (in [conversions.js](conversions.js)), but can be converted
by means of sub-conversions (e.g. XYZ -> **RGB** -> CMYK), are automatically routed together. This allows just about any
 color model supported by `color-convert` to be converted to any other model, so long as a sub-conversion path exists. This is also
 true for conversions requiring more than one step in between (e.g. LCH -> **LAB** -> **XYZ** -> **RGB** ->
Hex).
...

function color-convert.hwb.hex.raw (args)

  • description and source-code
    raw = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		return fn(args);
	}
  • example usage
    ...

 (not including alpha).

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

// Hex to LAB
convert.hex.lab('DEADBF');         // [ 76, 21, -2 ]
convert.hex.lab.raw('DEADBF');     // [ 75.56213190997677, 20.653827952644754, -2.290532499330533 ]

// RGB to CMYK
convert.rgb.cmyk(167, 255, 4);     // [ 35, 0, 98, 0 ]
convert.rgb.cmyk.raw(167, 255, 4); // [ 34.509803921568626, 0, 98.43137254901961, 0 ]
```

Color-convert is a color conversion library for JavaScript and node.
It converts all ways between `rgb`, `hsl`, `hsv`, `hwb`, `cmyk`, `ansi`, `ansi16`, `hex` strings, and CSS `keyword`s (will round
 to closest):

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hsl(140, 200, 100);             // [96, 48, 59]
convert.keyword.rgb('blue');                // [0, 0, 255]

var rgbChannels = convert.rgb.channels;     // 3
var cmykChannels = convert.cmyk.channels;   // 4
var ansiChannels = convert.ansi16.channels; // 1
```

All functions that accept multiple arguments also support passing an array.

Note that this does **not** apply to functions that convert from a color that only requires one value (e.g. `keyword`, `ansi256`, `
hex`, etc.)

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hex(123, 45, 67);      // '7B2D43'
convert.rgb.hex([123, 45, 67]);    // '7B2D43'
```

## Routing

Conversions that don't have an _explicitly_ defined conversion (in [conversions.js](conversions.js)), but can be converted
by means of sub-conversions (e.g. XYZ -> **RGB** -> CMYK), are automatically routed together. This allows just about any
 color model supported by `color-convert` to be converted to any other model, so long as a sub-conversion path exists. This is also
 true for conversions requiring more than one step in between (e.g. LCH -> **LAB** -> **XYZ** -> **RGB** ->
Hex).
...

function color-convert.keyword.hsl (args)

  • description and source-code
    hsl = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}
  • example usage
    ...

		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}

All functions that accept multiple arguments also support passing an array.

hex`, etc.)

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hex(123, 45, 67);      // '7B2D43'
convert.rgb.hex([123, 45, 67]);    // '7B2D43'
```

## Routing

Conversions that don't have an _explicitly_ defined conversion (in [conversions.js](conversions.js)), but can be converted
by means of sub-conversions (e.g. XYZ -> **RGB** -> CMYK), are automatically routed together. This allows just about any
 color model supported by `color-convert` to be converted to any other model, so long as a sub-conversion path exists. This is also
 true for conversions requiring more than one step in between (e.g. LCH -> **LAB** -> **XYZ** -> **RGB** ->
Hex).
...

function color-convert.keyword.hex.raw (args)

  • description and source-code
    raw = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		return fn(args);
	}
  • example usage

  • example usage
    ...

Color-convert is a color conversion library for JavaScript and node.
It converts all ways between `rgb`, `hsl`, `hsv`, `hwb`, `cmyk`, `ansi`, `ansi16`, `hex` strings, and CSS `keyword`s (will round
 to closest):

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hsl(140, 200, 100);             // [96, 48, 59]
convert.keyword.rgb('blue');                // [0, 0, 255]

var rgbChannels = convert.rgb.channels;     // 3
var cmykChannels = convert.cmyk.channels;   // 4
var ansiChannels = convert.ansi16.channels; // 1
```
...

			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		return fn(args);
	}
  • example usage

### Arrays
All functions that accept multiple arguments also support passing an array.

Note that this does **not** apply to functions that convert from a color that only requires one value (e.g. `keyword`, `ansi256`, `
hex`, etc.)

All functions that accept multiple arguments also support passing an array.

Note that this does **not** apply to functions that convert from a color that only requires one value (e.g. `keyword`, `ansi256`, `
hex`, etc.)

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hex(123, 45, 67);      // '7B2D43'
convert.rgb.hex([123, 45, 67]);    // '7B2D43'
```

## Routing

Conversions that don't have an _explicitly_ defined conversion (in [conversions.js](conversions.js)), but can be converted
by means of sub-conversions (e.g. XYZ -> **RGB** -> CMYK), are automatically routed together. This allows just about any
 color model supported by `color-convert` to be converted to any other model, so long as a sub-conversion path exists. This is also
 true for conversions requiring more than one step in between (e.g. LCH -> **LAB** -> **XYZ** -> **RGB** ->
Hex).
...

function color-convert.lab.hsl (args)

  • description and source-code
    hsl = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}
  • example usage
    ...

Color-convert is a color conversion library for JavaScript and node.
It converts all ways between `rgb`, `hsl`, `hsv`, `hwb`, `cmyk`, `ansi`, `ansi16`, `hex` strings, and CSS `keyword`s (will round
 to closest):

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hsl(140, 200, 100);             // [96, 48, 59]
convert.keyword.rgb('blue');                // [0, 0, 255]

var rgbChannels = convert.rgb.channels;     // 3
var cmykChannels = convert.cmyk.channels;   // 4
var ansiChannels = convert.ansi16.channels; // 1
```
...

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {

			}
		}

		return result;
	}
  • example usage
    ...
	return [l, a, b];
};

convert.rgb.ansi16 = function (args) {
	var r = args[0];
	var g = args[1];
	var b = args[2];
	var value = 1 in arguments ? arguments[1] : convert.rgb.hsv(args)[2]; // hsv ->
ansi16 optimization

	value = Math.round(value / 50);

	if (value === 0) {
		return 30;
	}

All functions that accept multiple arguments also support passing an array.

Note that this does **not** apply to functions that convert from a color that only requires one value (e.g. `keyword`, `ansi256`, `
hex`, etc.)

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hex(123, 45, 67);      // '7B2D43'
convert.rgb.hex([123, 45, 67]);    // '7B2D43'
```

## Routing

Conversions that don't have an _explicitly_ defined conversion (in [conversions.js](conversions.js)), but can be converted
by means of sub-conversions (e.g. XYZ -> **RGB** -> CMYK), are automatically routed together. This allows just about any
 color model supported by `color-convert` to be converted to any other model, so long as a sub-conversion path exists. This is also
 true for conversions requiring more than one step in between (e.g. LCH -> **LAB** -> **XYZ** -> **RGB** ->
Hex).
...

function color-convert.lab.hex.raw (args)

  • description and source-code
    raw = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		return fn(args);
	}

Color-convert is a color conversion library for JavaScript and node.
It converts all ways between `rgb`, `hsl`, `hsv`, `hwb`, `cmyk`, `ansi`, `ansi16`, `hex` strings, and CSS `keyword`s (will round
 to closest):

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hsl(140, 200, 100);             // [96, 48, 59]
convert.keyword.rgb('blue');                // [0, 0, 255]

var rgbChannels = convert.rgb.channels;     // 3
var cmykChannels = convert.cmyk.channels;   // 4
var ansiChannels = convert.ansi16.channels; // 1
```

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}
  • example usage
    ...
All functions that accept multiple arguments also support passing an array.

Note that this does **not** apply to functions that convert from a color that only requires one value (e.g. `keyword`, `ansi256`, `
hex`, etc.)

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hex(123, 45, 67);      // '7B2D43'
convert.rgb.hex([123, 45, 67]);    // '7B2D43'
```

## Routing

Conversions that don't have an _explicitly_ defined conversion (in [conversions.js](conversions.js)), but can be converted
by means of sub-conversions (e.g. XYZ -> **RGB** -> CMYK), are automatically routed together. This allows just about any
 color model supported by `color-convert` to be converted to any other model, so long as a sub-conversion path exists. This is also
 true for conversions requiring more than one step in between (e.g. LCH -> **LAB** -> **XYZ** -> **RGB** ->
Hex).
...

function color-convert.lch.hsl (args)

  • description and source-code
    hsl = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}
  • example usage
    ...

Color-convert is a color conversion library for JavaScript and node.
It converts all ways between `rgb`, `hsl`, `hsv`, `hwb`, `cmyk`, `ansi`, `ansi16`, `hex` strings, and CSS `keyword`s (will round
 to closest):

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hsl(140, 200, 100);             // [96, 48, 59]
convert.keyword.rgb('blue');                // [0, 0, 255]

var rgbChannels = convert.rgb.channels;     // 3
var cmykChannels = convert.cmyk.channels;   // 4
var ansiChannels = convert.ansi16.channels; // 1
```
...

	var g = args[1];
	var b = args[2];
	var value = 1 in arguments ? arguments[1] : convert.rgb.hsv(args)[2]; // hsv ->
ansi16 optimization

	value = Math.round(value / 50);

	if (value === 0) {
		return 30;
	}

convert.hex.lab('DEADBF');         // [ 76, 21, -2 ]
convert.hex.lab.raw('DEADBF');     // [ 75.56213190997677, 20.653827952644754
, -2.290532499330533 ]

// RGB to CMYK
convert.rgb.cmyk(167, 255, 4);     // [ 35, 0, 98, 0 ]
convert.rgb.cmyk.raw(167, 255, 4); // [ 34.509803921568626, 0, 98.43137254901961, 0 ]
```

module color-convert.lch.hsv

function color-convert.lch.hsv (args)

  • description and source-code
    hsv = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}
  • example usage

	return [l, a, b];
};

convert.rgb.ansi16 = function (args) {
	var r = args[0];
	var g = args[1];
	var b = args[2];
	var value = 1 in arguments ? arguments[1] : convert.rgb.hsv(args)[2]; // hsv ->
ansi16 optimization

	value = Math.round(value / 50);

	if (value === 0) {
		return 30;
	}

  • example usage
    ...
Color-convert is a color conversion library for JavaScript and node.
It converts all ways between `rgb`, `hsl`, `hsv`, `hwb`, `cmyk`, `ansi`, `ansi16`, `hex` strings, and CSS `keyword`s (will round
 to closest):

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hsl(140, 200, 100);             // [96, 48, 59]
convert.keyword.rgb('blue');                // [0, 0, 255]

var rgbChannels = convert.rgb.channels;     // 3
var cmykChannels = convert.cmyk.channels;   // 4
var ansiChannels = convert.ansi16.channels; // 1
```

### Arrays
All functions that accept multiple arguments also support passing an array.

Note that this does **not** apply to functions that convert from a color that only requires one value (e.g. `keyword`, `ansi256`, `
hex`, etc.)

All functions that accept multiple arguments also support passing an array.

Note that this does **not** apply to functions that convert from a color that only requires one value (e.g. `keyword`, `ansi256`, `
hex`, etc.)

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hex(123, 45, 67);      // '7B2D43'
convert.rgb.hex([123, 45, 67]);    // '7B2D43'
```

## Routing

Conversions that don't have an _explicitly_ defined conversion (in [conversions.js](conversions.js)), but can be converted
by means of sub-conversions (e.g. XYZ -> **RGB** -> CMYK), are automatically routed together. This allows just about any
 color model supported by `color-convert` to be converted to any other model, so long as a sub-conversion path exists. This is also
 true for conversions requiring more than one step in between (e.g. LCH -> **LAB** -> **XYZ** -> **RGB** ->
Hex).
...

function color-convert.rgb.hsl (args)

  • description and source-code
    hsl = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}
  • example usage
    ...

 (not including alpha).

convert.rgb.hex(123, 45, 67);      // '7B2D43'
convert.rgb.hex([123, 45, 67]);    // '7B2D43'
```

## Routing

Conversions that don't have an _explicitly_ defined conversion (in [conversions.js](conversions.js)), but can be converted
by means of sub-conversions (e.g. XYZ -> **RGB** -> CMYK), are automatically routed together. This allows just about any
 color model supported by `color-convert` to be converted to any other model, so long as a sub-conversion path exists. This is also
 true for conversions requiring more than one step in between (e.g. LCH -> **LAB** -> **XYZ** -> **RGB** ->
Hex).
...

function color-convert.rgb.hex.raw (args)

  • description and source-code
    raw = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		return fn(args);
	}
  • example usage
    ...
All 'from' functions have a hidden property called `.channels` that indicates the number of channels the function expects

  • example usage
    ...

Color-convert is a color conversion library for JavaScript and node.
It converts all ways between `rgb`, `hsl`, `hsv`, `hwb`, `cmyk`, `ansi`, `ansi16`, `hex` strings, and CSS `keyword`s (will round
 to closest):

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hsl(140, 200, 100);             // [96, 48, 59]
convert.keyword.rgb('blue');                // [0, 0, 255]

var rgbChannels = convert.rgb.channels;     // 3
var cmykChannels = convert.cmyk.channels;   // 4
var ansiChannels = convert.ansi16.channels; // 1
```
...

			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}
  • example usage
    ...

All 'from' functions have a hidden property called `.channels` that indicates the number of channels the function expects
 (not including alpha).

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

// Hex to LAB
convert.hex.lab('DEADBF');         // [ 76, 21, -2 ]
convert.hex.lab.raw('DEADBF');     // [ 75.56213190997677, 20.653827952644754, -2.290532499330533 ]

// RGB to CMYK
convert.rgb.cmyk(167, 255, 4);     // [ 35, 0, 98, 0 ]
convert.rgb.cmyk.raw(167, 255, 4); // [ 34.509803921568626, 0, 98.43137254901961, 0 ]
```

All functions that accept multiple arguments also support passing an array.

Note that this does **not** apply to functions that convert from a color that only requires one value (e.g. `keyword`, `ansi256`, `
hex`, etc.)

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hex(123, 45, 67);      // '7B2D43'
convert.rgb.hex([123, 45, 67]);    // '7B2D43'
```

## Routing

Conversions that don't have an _explicitly_ defined conversion (in [conversions.js](conversions.js)), but can be converted
by means of sub-conversions (e.g. XYZ -> **RGB** -> CMYK), are automatically routed together. This allows just about any
 color model supported by `color-convert` to be converted to any other model, so long as a sub-conversion path exists. This is also
 true for conversions requiring more than one step in between (e.g. LCH -> **LAB** -> **XYZ** -> **RGB** ->
Hex).
...

function color-convert.xyz.hsl (args)

  • description and source-code
    hsl = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}
  • example usage
    ...

Color-convert is a color conversion library for JavaScript and node.
It converts all ways between `rgb`, `hsl`, `hsv`, `hwb`, `cmyk`, `ansi`, `ansi16`, `hex` strings, and CSS `keyword`s (will round
 to closest):

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hsl(140, 200, 100);             // [96, 48, 59]
convert.keyword.rgb('blue');                // [0, 0, 255]

var rgbChannels = convert.rgb.channels;     // 3
var cmykChannels = convert.cmyk.channels;   // 4
var ansiChannels = convert.ansi16.channels; // 1
```
...

			}
		}

		return result;
	}

	var g = args[1];

ansi16 optimization

	value = Math.round(value / 50);

	if (value === 0) {
		return 30;
	}

All 'from' functions have a hidden property called `.channels` that indicates the number of channels the function expects
 (not including alpha).

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

// Hex to LAB
convert.hex.lab('DEADBF');         // [ 76, 21, -2 ]
convert.hex.lab.raw('DEADBF');     // [ 75.56213190997677, 20.653827952644754
, -2.290532499330533 ]

// RGB to CMYK
convert.rgb.cmyk(167, 255, 4);     // [ 35, 0, 98, 0 ]
convert.rgb.cmyk.raw(167, 255, 4); // [ 34.509803921568626, 0, 98.43137254901961, 0 ]
```

function color-convert.xyz.cmyk (args)

  • description and source-code
    cmyk = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		var result = fn(args);

		// we're assuming the result is an array here.
		// see notice in conversions.js; don't use box types
		// in conversion functions.
		if (typeof result === 'object') {
			for (var len = result.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
				result[i] = Math.round(result[i]);
			}
		}

		return result;
	}

convert.rgb.hex(123, 45, 67);      // '7B2D43'
convert.rgb.hex([123, 45, 67]);    // '7B2D43'
```

## Routing

Conversions that don't have an _explicitly_ defined conversion (in [conversions.js](conversions.js)), but can be converted
by means of sub-conversions (e.g. XYZ -> **RGB** -> CMYK), are automatically routed together. This allows just about any
 color model supported by `color-convert` to be converted to any other model, so long as a sub-conversion path exists. This is also
 true for conversions requiring more than one step in between (e.g. LCH -> **LAB** -> **XYZ** -> **RGB** ->
Hex).
...

function color-convert.xyz.hex.raw (args)

  • description and source-code
    raw = function (args) {
		if (args === undefined || args === null) {
			return args;
		}

		if (arguments.length > 1) {
			args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
		}

		return fn(args);
	}
  • example usage

  • example usage
    ...

Color-convert is a color conversion library for JavaScript and node.
It converts all ways between `rgb`, `hsl`, `hsv`, `hwb`, `cmyk`, `ansi`, `ansi16`, `hex` strings, and CSS `keyword`s (will round
 to closest):

```js
var convert = require('color-convert');

convert.rgb.hsl(140, 200, 100);             // [96, 48, 59]
convert.keyword.rgb('blue');                // [0, 0, 255]

var rgbChannels = convert.rgb.channels;     // 3
var cmykChannels = convert.cmyk.channels;   // 4
var ansiChannels = convert.ansi16.channels; // 1
```
...

		}

		return fn(args);
	}
